<br>
I'd like to thank everyone for their responces on this issue, and it's really helped me to clarify my position.  Ah...clarity...if only.  Well, soon.  Sorry, brief enchanter reverie.<br>
<br>
After reading everyone's thoughts, I don't feel there's a need to throw this person (or anyone else) on any public blacklist.  As has been pointed out before, and wisely, we benefit from the low server population and it has been amply demonstrated that reputations get ruined very quickly with no one in particular attacking them constantly.  Word of month spreads quickly.  If anyone of the higher end-gamers seeks my in-put on who might not be worthy of great generosity (such as Windroll has already requested) I'll be happy to provide, but only on an individual basis.  I do tend to notice the auction channels more, if only because I spend a fair amount of time hawking jewelry.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Regarding my trade practices and pricing, I'll just clarify (sigh, clarity) what I meant when I said I was pricing gold jewelry at a loss right now.  I'm skilling into it, which means I fail often.  These same prices will bring me profit later on, which is the pattern I followed with electrum.  I have a whole website dedicated to fair jewelcraft pricing at www.tradersjewelry.freeservers.com.  Check it out, if you wish.  It explains all my pricing, as well as making it publicly available for scrutiny.<br>
<br>
Finally, let me thank everyone for their kind comments towards the Traders Union.  It is wonderful to see the good reputation we established along the way, and all the people who remember us after only one or two transactions.  That's all it takes to make all that auctioning worthwhile.<br>
<br>
I am about to post another thread regarding the Traders Union, and rather than hijack this thread (which seems to be drying up of natural causes) I'll just ask everyone interested in the business of my guild to read that post.<br>
<br>
Thank you all again.  Good travels, and best wishes.<br>
<br>
Valquiss Silverpalm<br>
First Officer of the Traders Union (in transition, please read the other thread for details)<br>
